.LI "\fBNAME\fP"
.br
upper, lower - translate a copy of a string to upper or lower case.
.LI "\fBSYNOPSIS\fP"
.br
.EX
\#include <sblib.h>

char *upper(char *string);
char *lower(char *string);
.EE
.LI "\fBDESCRIPTION\fP"
.br
The \*(Ur and \*(Lr functions translate the case of \fIstring\fP.
The \*(Ur function copies the string, translating any lower case
characters to upper case and returns the result.
The \*(Lr function copies the string, translating any upper case
characters to lower case and returns the result.
The returned string is dynamically allocated but \*(Ur and \*(Lr
are responsible for freeing them.  Do not free or delete the returned
strings in application code.
